The committee, in a communique  in Akure yesterday signed by its Chairman, Senator Olorunnimbe Farukanmi, also commended the governor for uniting all aggrieved factions in the state. The elders urged other asprants that participated in the primary to co-operate with the governor in all respects. IN another development, the Yoruba World Congress (YWC) has commended Akeredolu for the official inauguration of the regional security outfit, code-named Amotekun Corps. he leader of the Congress, Prof. Banji Akintoye, who gave the commendation yesterday, said that the move showed that the governor was serious about the security initiative and not engaged in mere lip service or political shenanigan. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .